nl: Si modelamos un pterosaurio con la masa del helicóptero más pesado de esta lista, ¿qué superficie alar teórica necesitaría si asumimos que tiene una eficiencia de sustentación equivalente al valor de carga discal más bajo entre estas aeronaves?
sql:
SELECT (
  SELECT CAST(REPLACE(SUBSTR(`Max Gross Weight`, INSTR(`Max Gross Weight`, `(`) + 1, INSTR(`Max Gross Weight`, ` kg`) - INSTR(`Max Gross Weight`, `(`) - 1), `,`, ``) AS REAL)
  FROM `table_1_10006830_1`
  ORDER BY CAST(REPLACE(SUBSTR(`Max Gross Weight`, INSTR(`Max Gross Weight`, `(`) + 1, INSTR(`Max Gross Weight`, ` kg`) - INSTR(`Max Gross Weight`, `(`) - 1), `,`, ``) AS REAL) DESC
  LIMIT 1
) / (
  SELECT CAST(SUBSTR(`Max disk Loading`, INSTR(`Max disk Loading`, `(`) + 1, INSTR(`Max disk Loading`, ` kg/m²)`) - INSTR(`Max disk Loading`, `(`) - 1) AS REAL)
  FROM `table_1_10006830_1`
  ORDER BY CAST(SUBSTR(`Max disk Loading`, INSTR(`Max disk Loading`, `(`) + 1, INSTR(`Max disk Loading`, ` kg/m²)`) - INSTR(`Max disk Loading`, `(`) - 1) AS REAL) ASC
  LIMIT 1
) AS `Theoretical_Pterosaur_Wing_Area_m2`;
db_sql: SELECT (SELECT CAST(REPLACE(SUBSTR(col2, INSTR(col2, '(') + 1, INSTR(col2, ' kg') - INSTR(col2, '(') - 1), ',', '') AS REAL) FROM `table_1_10006830_1` ORDER BY CAST(REPLACE(SUBSTR(col2, INSTR(col2, '(') + 1, INSTR(col2, ' kg') - INSTR(col2, '(') - 1), ',', '') AS REAL) DESC LIMIT 1) / (SELECT CAST(SUBSTR(col4, INSTR(col4, '(') + 1, INSTR(col4, ' kg/m²)') - INSTR(col4, '(') - 1) AS REAL) FROM `table_1_10006830_1` ORDER BY CAST(SUBSTR(col4, INSTR(col4, '(') + 1, INSTR(col4, ' kg/m²)') - INSTR(col4, '(') - 1) AS REAL) ASC LIMIT 1) AS `Theoretical_Pterosaur_Wing_Area_m2`;

nl: Compara los dos vectores para los años críticos del 33, 34 y 35. Genera una tabla que muestre el recuento de casos en bruto y la tasa de cambio anual para el Tifus como 'indicador de hambruna' justo al lado de los mismos datos para la Malaria como 'indicador ecológico'.
sql:
WITH LaggedData AS (
  SELECT
    `Year`,
    `Typhus`,
    CAST(REPLACE(`Malaria`, ' (avg)', '') AS REAL) AS `Malaria_Clean`,
    LAG(`Typhus`, 1) OVER (ORDER BY `Year`) AS `Prev_Typhus`,
    LAG(CAST(REPLACE(`Malaria`, ' (avg)', '') AS REAL), 1) OVER (ORDER BY `Year`) AS `Prev_Malaria`
  FROM
    `table_1_1007688_1`
)
SELECT
  `Year`,
  `Typhus` AS `Typhus_Famine_Indicator`,
  ROUND(((`Typhus` - `Prev_Typhus`) * 100.0 / `Prev_Typhus`), 2) AS `Typhus_YoY_Change_%`,
  `Malaria_Clean` AS `Malaria_Ecological_Indicator`,
  ROUND(((`Malaria_Clean` - `Prev_Malaria`) * 100.0 / `Prev_Malaria`), 2) AS `Malaria_YoY_Change_%`
FROM
  LaggedData
WHERE
  CAST(SUBSTR(`Year`, 1, 4) AS INTEGER) IN (1933, 1934, 1935);
db_sql:
WITH LaggedData AS (
  SELECT
    col0,
    col1,
    CAST(REPLACE(col5, ' (avg)', '') AS REAL) AS `Malaria_Clean`,
    LAG(col1, 1) OVER (ORDER BY col0) AS `Prev_Typhus`,
    LAG(CAST(REPLACE(col5, ' (avg)', '') AS REAL), 1) OVER (ORDER BY col0) AS `Prev_Malaria`
  FROM
    `table_1_1007688_1`
)
SELECT
  col0,
  col1 AS `Typhus_Famine_Indicator`,
  ROUND(((col1 - `Prev_Typhus`) * 100.0 / `Prev_Typhus`), 2) AS `Typhus_YoY_Change_%`,
  `Malaria_Clean` AS `Malaria_Ecological_Indicator`,
  ROUND(((`Malaria_Clean` - `Prev_Malaria`) * 100.0 / `Prev_Malaria`), 2) AS `Malaria_YoY_Change_%`
FROM
  LaggedData
WHERE
  CAST(SUBSTR(col0, 1, 4) AS INTEGER) IN (1933, 1934, 1935);

nl: Identifica cualquier grupo demográfico, además del de 'Edades 5-14', que deba ser etiquetado como de 'Alto Riesgo'. Define 'Alto Riesgo' como tener a más de la mitad de los niños económicamente activos involucrados en trabajos peligrosos, y clasifica los resultados de mayor a menor riesgo.
sql:
SELECT
  `` AS `Demographic`,
  CASE
    WHEN (`Children In Hazardous Work (000s)` * 1.0 / `Economically Active Children (000s)`) > 0.5 THEN `High Risk`
  END AS `Risk_Status`
FROM
  `table_1_101942_2`
WHERE
  `` != `Ages 5–14`
ORDER BY
  (`Children In Hazardous Work (000s)` * 1.0 / `Economically Active Children (000s)`) DESC;
db_sql:

  col0 AS `Demographic`,

    WHEN (col6 * 1.0 / col2) > 0.5 THEN 'High Risk'
  END `Risk_Status`

WHERE
  col0 != 'Ages 5–14'
ORDER BY
  (col6 * 1.0 / col2) DESC;

nl: Para los segmentos de su carrera de preguerra y posguerra, muéstrame su promedio de goles en liga, su ratio de goles por partido en la FA Cup y el porcentaje de sus goles totales que marcó en la copa.
sql:
SELECT
  CASE
    WHEN `Season` IN ('1913–14', '1914–15')
    THEN 'Pre-War'
    ELSE 'Post-War'
  END AS `Career_Period`,
  AVG(`League Goals`) AS `Avg_League_Goals`,
  SUM(`FA Cup Goals`) * 1.0 / SUM(`FA Cup Apps`) AS `FA_Cup_Goals_Per_Game`,
  SUM(`FA Cup Goals`) * 1.0 / SUM(`Total Goals`) AS `FA_Cup_Share_of_Total_Goals`
FROM
  `table_1_10240125_2`
GROUP BY
  `Career_Period`;
db_sql:
SELECT
  CASE
    WHEN col0 IN ('1913–14', '1914–15')
    THEN 'Pre-War'
    ELSE 'Post-War'
  END AS `Career_Period`,
  AVG(col3) AS `Avg_League_Goals`,
  SUM(col5) * 1.0 / SUM(col4) AS `FA_Cup_Goals_Per_Game`,
  SUM(col5) * 1.0 / SUM(col7) AS `FA_Cup_Share_of_Total_Goals`
FROM
  `table_1_10240125_2`
GROUP BY
  `Career_Period`;

  SUM(CASE WHEN STRFTIME('%Y', `Season`) > '1919' THEN `League Apps` ELSE 0 END) AS `Post-War League Apps`

nl: Para los años en que a más de 2000 jamaicanos se les concedió la ciudadanía británica, ¿cuál fue el total combinado de naturalizaciones por residencia y por matrimonio, y cuál de esas dos vías fue más dominante? Por favor, muestra primero los años con los totales combinados más altos.
sql:
SELECT
  `Year`,
  `Naturalisation by residence` + `Naturalisation by marriage` AS `Main_Pathways_Total`,
  CASE
    WHEN CAST(`Naturalisation by residence` AS REAL) > `Naturalisation by marriage`
    THEN `Residence was dominant`
    ELSE `Marriage was dominant or equal`
  END AS `Dominant_Pathway_Comparison`
FROM
  `table_1_11214212_1`
WHERE
  `Numer of Jamaicans granted British citizenship` > `2000`
ORDER BY
  `Main_Pathways_Total` DESC;
db_sql: SELECT col0, col2 + col3 AS `Main_Pathways_Total`, CASE WHEN col2 > col3 THEN 'Residence was dominant' ELSE 'Marriage was dominant or equal' END AS `Dominant_Pathway_Comparison` FROM `table_1_11214212_1` WHERE col1 > 2000 ORDER BY `Main_Pathways_Total` DESC;

nl: Bien, generemos el conjunto de datos final para mi artículo. Por favor, proporciona una lista de todas las Grandes Finales en el Stadium Australia donde el equipo no favorito (definido por tener menos apariciones previas) resultó victorioso, ordenada principalmente por el margen de puntos más estrecho y secundariamente por la mayor asistencia. Esto nos dará la visión más clara de la resonancia emocional en acción.
sql: WITH `TeamAppearances` AS (SELECT CASE WHEN INSTR(`Team`, ' (') > 0 THEN SUBSTR(`Team`, 1, INSTR(`Team`, ' (') - 1) ELSE `Team` END AS `BaseTeam`, COUNT(*) AS `TotalAppearances` FROM (SELECT `WinningTeam` AS `Team` FROM `table_1_11236195_5` UNION ALL SELECT `LosingTeam` AS `Team` FROM `table_1_11236195_5`) GROUP BY `BaseTeam`) SELECT T1.`Season`, T1.`WinningTeam`, T1.`LosingTeam`, T1.`GF Attendance`, CAST(SUBSTR(T1.`Score`, 1, INSTR(T1.`Score`, '-') - 1) AS REAL) - CAST(SUBSTR(T1.`Score`, INSTR(T1.`Score`, '-') + 1) AS REAL) AS `PointMargin`, WA.`TotalAppearances` AS `WinnerAppearances`, LA.`TotalAppearances` AS `LoserAppearances` FROM `table_1_11236195_5` AS T1 JOIN `TeamAppearances` AS WA ON (CASE WHEN INSTR(T1.`WinningTeam`, ' (') > 0 THEN SUBSTR(T1.`WinningTeam`, 1, INSTR(T1.`WinningTeam`, ' (') - 1) ELSE T1.`WinningTeam` END) = WA.`BaseTeam` JOIN `TeamAppearances` AS LA ON (CASE WHEN INSTR(T1.`LosingTeam`, ' (') > 0 THEN SUBSTR(T1.`LosingTeam`, 1, INSTR(T1.`LosingTeam`, ' (') - 1) ELSE T1.`LosingTeam` END) = LA.`BaseTeam` WHERE T1.`Location` LIKE '%Stadium Australia%' AND WA.`TotalAppearances` < LA.`TotalAppearances` ORDER BY `PointMargin` ASC, T1.`GF Attendance` DESC;
db_sql: WITH `TeamAppearances` AS (SELECT CASE WHEN INSTR(`Team`, ' (') > 0 THEN SUBSTR(`Team`, 1, INSTR(`Team`, ' (') - 1) ELSE `Team` END AS `BaseTeam`, COUNT(*) AS `TotalAppearances` FROM (SELECT col2 AS `Team` FROM `table_1_11236195_5` UNION ALL SELECT col4 AS `Team` FROM `table_1_11236195_5`) GROUP BY `BaseTeam`) SELECT T1.col0, T1.col2, T1.col4, T1.col6, CAST(SUBSTR(T1.col3, 1, INSTR(T1.col3, '-') - 1) AS REAL) - CAST(SUBSTR(T1.col3, INSTR(T1.col3, '-') + 1) AS REAL) AS `PointMargin`, WA.`TotalAppearances` AS `WinnerAppearances`, LA.`TotalAppearances` AS `LoserAppearances` FROM `table_1_11236195_5` AS T1 JOIN `TeamAppearances` AS WA ON (CASE WHEN INSTR(T1.col2, ' (') > 0 THEN SUBSTR(T1.col2, 1, INSTR(T1.col2, ' (') - 1) ELSE T1.col2 END) = WA.`BaseTeam` JOIN `TeamAppearances` AS LA ON (CASE WHEN INSTR(T1.col4, ' (') > 0 THEN SUBSTR(T1.col4, 1, INSTR(T1.col4, ' (') - 1) ELSE T1.col4 END) = LA.`BaseTeam` WHERE T1.col5 LIKE '%Stadium Australia%' AND WA.`TotalAppearances` < LA.`TotalAppearances` ORDER BY `PointMargin` ASC, T1.col6 DESC;

nl: Me interesan los modelos de motor que usan combustible de 80/87 octanos. ¿Puedes encontrar relaciones de compresión que sean utilizadas por tres o más de estos modelos y darme los nombres de los motores?
sql:
SELECT
  GROUP_CONCAT(`Engine`) AS `Grouped_Engines`,
  `Compression ratio`
FROM
  `table_1_1123802_1`
WHERE
  `Octane rating` = `80/87`
GROUP BY
  `Compression ratio`
HAVING
  COUNT(`Engine`) > 2
ORDER BY
  `Supercharger gear ratio` DESC;
db_sql:
SELECT
  GROUP_CONCAT(col0),
  col4
FROM
  `table_1_1123802_1`
WHERE
  col6 = '80/87'
GROUP BY
  col4
HAVING
  COUNT(col0) > 2
ORDER BY
  col5 DESC;
db_result: [('wasp jr. sb,wasp jr. t1b2,wasp jr. b4', '6.0:1')]

nl: Necesito ver una lista de personajes y sus sucesores inmediatos. Para crear esta lista, primero separa los personajes en tres líneas de tiempo: una para los conectados con Taylor, una para Flack y una para el resto. Ordena cada línea de tiempo por su primera aparición. Luego, dame los cinco pares principales de personajes de estas líneas de tiempo, ordenados del más reciente al más antiguo según cuándo apareció el primer personaje del par.
sql: WITH `RankedAppearances` AS (SELECT `Character`, `Relationship`, `First appearance`, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY (CASE WHEN `Relationship` LIKE `%Taylor%` THEN 1 WHEN `Relationship` LIKE `%Flack%` THEN 2 ELSE 3 END) ORDER BY `First appearance` ASC) AS `Rank` FROM `table_1_11240028_3`) SELECT T1.`Character` AS `Preceding Character`, T2.`Character` AS `Succeeding Character` FROM `RankedAppearances` AS T1 LEFT OUTER JOIN `RankedAppearances` AS T2 ON T1.`Rank` + 1 = T2.`Rank` WHERE T1.`Character` IS NOT T2.`Character` AND EXISTS (SELECT * FROM `table_1_11240028_3` AS T3 WHERE T3.`Character` IS NOT NULL OR T3.`Relationship` ISNULL) GROUP BY `Preceding Character`, `Succeeding Character` HAVING T1.`Character` IS NOT NULL AND T2.`Character` IS NOT NULL ORDER BY T1.`First appearance` DESC, T2.`First appearance` ASC LIMIT 5 OFFSET 0;
db_sql: WITH `RankedAppearances` AS (SELECT col0, col3, CASE WHEN col2 LIKE '%Taylor%' THEN 1 WHEN col2 LIKE '%Flack%' THEN 2 ELSE 3 END AS `part`, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY CASE WHEN col2 LIKE '%Taylor%' THEN 1 WHEN col2 LIKE '%Flack%' THEN 2 ELSE 3 END ORDER BY col3 ASC) AS `rnk` FROM `table_1_11240028_3`) SELECT T1.col0 AS `Preceding Character`, T2.col0 AS `Succeeding Character` FROM `RankedAppearances` AS T1 INNER JOIN `RankedAppearances` AS T2 ON T1.`part` = T2.`part` AND T1.`rnk` + 1 = T2.`rnk` WHERE TRUE GROUP BY T1.col0, T2.col0, T1.col3, T2.col3 ORDER BY T1.col3 DESC, T2.col3 ASC LIMIT 5 OFFSET 0;
db_result: [('terrence davis', 'samantha flack'), ('ellie danville', 'russ josephson'), ('reed garrett', 'claire conrad taylor'), ('rikki sandoval', 'ellie danville')]

nl: Identifica las cuatro perturbaciones más significativas en el flujo metafísico. Para cada evento, enumera su clave, su fecha, la línea base de energía de la semana anterior, la lectura actual y la magnitud final del flujo.
sql: WITH MetaphysicalFlux AS (SELECT `Episode`, `Air Date`, CAST(`Viewers (m)` AS REAL) AS `Viewers`, LAG(CAST(`Viewers (m)` AS REAL), 1, 0) OVER (ORDER BY `No.`) AS `PreviousViewers` FROM `table_1_11274401_3`) SELECT `Episode` AS `Event_Key`, `Air Date` AS `Event_Date`, `PreviousViewers`, `Viewers` AS `CurrentViewers`, (`Viewers` - `PreviousViewers`) AS `Flux_Magnitude` FROM MetaphysicalFlux WHERE `PreviousViewers` > 0 ORDER BY ABS(`Flux_Magnitude`) DESC LIMIT 4;
db_sql: WITH MetaphysicalFlux AS (SELECT col1, col2, CAST(col7 AS REAL) AS `Viewers`, LAG(CAST(col7 AS REAL), 1, 0) OVER (ORDER BY col0) AS `PreviousViewers` FROM `table_1_11274401_3`) SELECT col1 AS `Event_Key`, col2 AS `Event_Date`, `PreviousViewers`, `Viewers` AS `CurrentViewers`, (`Viewers` - `PreviousViewers`) AS `Flux_Magnitude` FROM MetaphysicalFlux WHERE `PreviousViewers` > 0 ORDER BY ABS(`Flux_Magnitude`) DESC LIMIT 4;

nl: Necesito trazar el ciclo completo de la victoria. Muéstrame el campeón de la categoría 'Open 1st VIII' de cada año, y luego dime cuál era su 'Nivel de Chi Fundacional' (es decir, el número total de victorias en carreras Sub-15 que consiguieron) exactamente tres años antes de su manifestación final de éxito.
sql:
WITH `U15_Energy_Focus` AS (
  SELECT `Crew` AS `year`, `school`, COUNT(*) AS `wins`
  FROM (
    SELECT `Crew`, `U15 1st IV` AS `school` FROM `table_1_11318462_5`
    UNION ALL
    SELECT `Crew`, `U15 2nd IV` AS `school` FROM `table_1_11318462_5`
    UNION ALL
    SELECT `Crew`, `U15 3rd IV` AS `school` FROM `table_1_11318462_5`
    UNION ALL
    SELECT `Crew`, `U15 4th IV` AS `school` FROM `table_1_11318462_5`
    UNION ALL
    SELECT `Crew`, `U15 5th IV` AS `school` FROM `table_1_11318462_5`
    UNION ALL
    SELECT `Crew`, `U15 6th IV` AS `school` FROM `table_1_11318462_5`
  )
  GROUP BY `year`, `school`
)
SELECT
  T1.`Crew` AS `Manifestation_Year`,
  T1.`Open 1st VIII` AS `Champion_School`,
  COALESCE(T2.`wins`, 0) AS `Foundational_Chi_Level_3_Years_Prior`
FROM `table_1_11318462_5` AS T1
LEFT JOIN `U15_Energy_Focus` AS T2
  ON T1.`Crew` = T2.`year` + 3 AND T1.`Open 1st VIII` = T2.`school`
ORDER BY
  T1.`Crew`;
db_sql:
WITH `U15_Energy_Focus` AS (
  SELECT col0 AS `year`, `school`, COUNT(*) AS `wins`
  FROM (
    SELECT col0, col7 AS `school` FROM `table_1_11318462_5`
    UNION ALL
    SELECT col0, col8 AS `school` FROM `table_1_11318462_5`
    UNION ALL
    SELECT col0, col9 AS `school` FROM `table_1_11318462_5`
    UNION ALL
    SELECT col0, col10 AS `school` FROM `table_1_11318462_5`
    UNION ALL
    SELECT col0, col11 AS `school` FROM `table_1_11318462_5`
    UNION ALL
    SELECT col0, col12 AS `school` FROM `table_1_11318462_5`
  )
  GROUP BY `year`, `school`
)
SELECT
  T1.col0 AS `Manifestation_Year`,
  T1.col1 AS `Champion_School`,
  COALESCE(T2.`wins`, 0) AS `Foundational_Chi_Level_3_Years_Prior`
FROM `table_1_11318462_5` AS T1
LEFT JOIN `U15_Energy_Focus` AS T2
  ON T1.col0 = T2.`year` + 3 AND T1.col1 = T2.`school`
ORDER BY
  T1.col0;

nl: Muéstrame el oponente, la fecha y el estado del partido (victoria o derrota) para cada encuentro que Ana Timotic jugó después de la edición de 2005.
sql:
SELECT
  `Opponent`,
  `Date`,
  CASE
    WHEN `Outcome` = `Win`
    THEN `VICTORY`
    ELSE `DEFEAT`
  END AS `match_status`
FROM
  `table_1_11326124_3`

nl: Para cada director que ha dirigido más de un episodio, clasifica su audiencia promedio en EE. UU. como por encima o por debajo del promedio general de la serie, y enuméralos en orden descendente de su audiencia promedio.
sql:
WITH `DirectorStats` AS (
  SELECT
    `Director`,
    AVG(CAST(`U.S. viewers (millions)` AS REAL)) AS `AverageViewers`
  FROM `table_1_11404452_1`
  GROUP BY
    `Director`
  HAVING
    COUNT(`Series #`) > 1
), `Overall` AS (
  SELECT
    AVG(CAST(`U.S. viewers (millions)` AS REAL)) AS `GlobalAverage`
  FROM `table_1_11404452_1`
)
SELECT
  `DirectorStats`.`Director`,
  CASE
    WHEN `DirectorStats`.`AverageViewers` > `Overall`.`GlobalAverage` THEN `Above Average`
    ELSE `Below Average`
  END
FROM `DirectorStats`, `Overall`
ORDER BY
  `DirectorStats`.`AverageViewers` DESC;
db_sql: WITH `DirectorStats` AS (SELECT col3, AVG(CAST(col4 AS REAL)) AS `AverageViewers` FROM `table_1_11404452_1` GROUP BY col3 HAVING COUNT(col0) > 1), `Overall` AS (SELECT AVG(CAST(col4 AS REAL)) AS `GlobalAverage` FROM `table_1_11404452_1`) SELECT `DirectorStats`.col3, CASE WHEN `DirectorStats`.`AverageViewers` > `Overall`.`GlobalAverage` THEN 'Above Average' ELSE 'Below Average' END AS `Performance` FROM `DirectorStats`, `Overall` ORDER BY `DirectorStats`.`AverageViewers` DESC;
db_result: [('james hayman', 'Above Average'), ('lev l. spiro', 'Below Average'), ('tricia brock', 'Below Average')]

nl: Si modelamos un pterosaurio con la masa del helicóptero más pesado de esta lista, ¿qué área alar teórica necesitaría si asumimos que tiene una eficiencia de sustentación equivalente al valor más bajo de carga discal entre estas aeronaves?
sql:
SELECT (
  SELECT CAST(REPLACE(SUBSTR(`Max Gross Weight`, INSTR(`Max Gross Weight`, '(') + 1, INSTR(`Max Gross Weight`, ' kg') - INSTR(`Max Gross Weight`, '(') - 1), ',', '') AS REAL)
  FROM `table_m_1765006446265_7db0c124_10006830_1`
  ORDER BY CAST(REPLACE(SUBSTR(`Max Gross Weight`, INSTR(`Max Gross Weight`, '(') + 1, INSTR(`Max Gross Weight`, ' kg') - INSTR(`Max Gross Weight`, '(') - 1), ',', '') AS REAL) DESC
  LIMIT 1
) / (
  SELECT (
    CAST(REPLACE(SUBSTR(`Max Gross Weight`, INSTR(`Max Gross Weight`, '(') + 1, INSTR(`Max Gross Weight`, ' kg') - INSTR(`Max Gross Weight`, '(') - 1), ',', '') AS REAL)
    / CAST(REPLACE(SUBSTR(`Total disk area`, INSTR(`Total disk area`, '(') + 1, INSTR(`Total disk area`, ' m²') - INSTR(`Total disk area`, '(') - 1), ',', '') AS REAL)
  ) AS disk_loading
  FROM `table_m_1765006446265_7db0c124_10006830_1`
  ORDER BY disk_loading ASC
  LIMIT 1
) AS `Theoretical_Pterosaur_Wing_Area_m2`;
db_sql:
SELECT (
  SELECT CAST(REPLACE(SUBSTR(col2, INSTR(col2, '(') + 1, INSTR(col2, ' kg') - INSTR(col2, '(') - 1), ',', '') AS REAL)
  FROM `table_m_1765006446265_7db0c124_10006830_1`
  ORDER BY CAST(REPLACE(SUBSTR(col2, INSTR(col2, '(') + 1, INSTR(col2, ' kg') - INSTR(col2, '(') - 1), ',', '') AS REAL) DESC
  LIMIT 1
) / (
  SELECT (
    CAST(REPLACE(SUBSTR(col2, INSTR(col2, '(') + 1, INSTR(col2, ' kg') - INSTR(col2, '(') - 1), ',', '') AS REAL)
    / CAST(REPLACE(SUBSTR(col3, INSTR(col3, '(') + 1, INSTR(col3, ' m²') - INSTR(col3, '(') - 1), ',', '') AS REAL)
  ) AS disk_loading
  FROM `table_m_1765006446265_7db0c124_10006830_1`
  ORDER BY disk_loading ASC
  LIMIT 1
) AS `Theoretical_Pterosaur_Wing_Area_m2`;

nl: Compara los dos vectores para los años críticos del 33, 34 y 35. Genera una tabla que muestre el recuento de casos brutos y la tasa de cambio anual para el indicador de hambruna 'Tifus' justo al lado de los mismos datos para el indicador ecológico 'Malaria'.
sql:
WITH LaggedData AS (
  SELECT
    `Year`,
    `Typhus`,
    CAST(REPLACE(`Malaria`, ' (avg)', '') AS REAL) AS `Malaria_Clean`,
    LAG(`Typhus`, 1) OVER (ORDER BY `Year`) AS `Prev_Typhus`,
    LAG(CAST(REPLACE(`Malaria`, ' (avg)', '') AS REAL), 1) OVER (ORDER BY `Year`) AS `Prev_Malaria`
  FROM
    `table_m_1765006521907_c1e19942_1007688_1`
)
SELECT
  `Year`,
  `Typhus` AS `Typhus_Famine_Indicator`,
  ROUND(((`Typhus` - `Prev_Typhus`) * 100.0 / `Prev_Typhus`), 2) AS `Typhus_YoY_Change_%`,
  `Malaria_Clean` AS `Malaria_Ecological_Indicator`,
  ROUND(((`Malaria_Clean` - `Prev_Malaria`) * 100.0 / `Prev_Malaria`), 2) AS `Malaria_YoY_Change_%`
FROM
  LaggedData
WHERE
  CAST(SUBSTR(`Year`, 1, 4) AS INTEGER) IN (1933, 1934, 1935);
db_sql:
WITH LaggedData AS (
  SELECT
    col0,
    col1,
    CAST(REPLACE(col4, ' (avg)', '') AS REAL) AS `Malaria_Clean`,
    LAG(col1, 1) OVER (ORDER BY col0) AS `Prev_Typhus`,
    LAG(CAST(REPLACE(col4, ' (avg)', '') AS REAL), 1) OVER (ORDER BY col0) AS `Prev_Malaria`
  FROM `table_m_1765006521907_c1e19942_1007688_1`
)
SELECT
  col0,
  col1 AS `Typhus_Famine_Indicator`,
  ROUND(((col1 - `Prev_Typhus`) * 100.0 / `Prev_Typhus`), 2) AS `Typhus_YoY_Change_%`,
  `Malaria_Clean` AS `Malaria_Ecological_Indicator`,
  ROUND(((`Malaria_Clean` - `Prev_Malaria`) * 100.0 / `Prev_Malaria`), 2) AS `Malaria_YoY_Change_%`
FROM
  LaggedData
WHERE
  CAST(SUBSTR(col0, 1, 4) AS INTEGER) IN (1933, 1934, 1935);

nl: No estamos construyendo un programa que sea flor de un día, sino una dinastía. Necesito ver qué escuelas han demostrado que pueden adaptarse y ganar a medida que sus comunidades han crecido. Fíltralo solo a las escuelas con campeonatos en diferentes categorías, y luego muéstrame cada categoría que han ganado y el año en que consiguieron esa primera victoria.
sql:
WITH `UnpivotedWinners` AS (
  SELECT `Start_Year`, `Class A` AS `School`, `Class A` AS `Classification` FROM `table_m_1765006726338_1f107b5e_10399701_2`
  UNION ALL
  SELECT `Start_Year`, `Class AA` AS `School`, `Class AA` AS `Classification` FROM `table_m_1765006726338_1f107b5e_10399701_2`
  UNION ALL
  SELECT `Start_Year`, `Class AAA` AS `School`, `Class AAA` AS `Classification` FROM `table_m_1765006726338_1f107b5e_10399701_2`
  UNION ALL
  SELECT `Start_Year`, `Class AAAA` AS `School`, `Class AAAA` AS `Classification` FROM `table_m_1765006726338_1f107b5e_10399701_2`
  UNION ALL
  SELECT `Start_Year`, `Class AAAAA` AS `School`, `Class AAAAA` AS `Classification` FROM `table_m_1765006726338_1f107b5e_10399701_2`
)
SELECT
  T1.`School`,
  T1.`Classification`,
  MIN(T1.`Start_Year`) AS `First_Year_Won_In_Class`
FROM `UnpivotedWinners` AS T1
WHERE
  T1.`School` IN (
    SELECT
      `School`
    FROM
      `UnpivotedWinners`
    GROUP BY
      `School`
    HAVING
      COUNT(DISTINCT `Classification`) > 1
  )
GROUP BY
  T1.`School`,
  T1.`Classification`
ORDER BY
  T1.`School`,
  `First_Year_Won_In_Class`;
db_sql:
WITH `UnpivotedWinners` AS (
  SELECT col5, col0 AS `School`, col0 AS `Classification` FROM `table_m_1765006726338_1f107b5e_10399701_2`
  UNION ALL
  SELECT col5, col1 AS `School`, col1 AS `Classification` FROM `table_m_1765006726338_1f107b5e_10399701_2`
  UNION ALL
  SELECT col5, col2 AS `School`, col2 AS `Classification` FROM `table_m_1765006726338_1f107b5e_10399701_2`
  UNION ALL
  SELECT col5, col3 AS `School`, col3 AS `Classification` FROM `table_m_1765006726338_1f107b5e_10399701_2`
  UNION ALL
  SELECT col5, col4 AS `School`, col4 AS `Classification` FROM `table_m_1765006726338_1f107b5e_10399701_2`
)
SELECT
  T1.`School`,
  T1.`Classification`,
  MIN(T1.col5) AS `First_Year_Won_In_Class`
FROM `UnpivotedWinners` AS T1
WHERE
  T1.`School` IN (
    SELECT
      `School`
    FROM
      `UnpivotedWinners`
    GROUP BY
      `School`
    HAVING
      COUNT(DISTINCT `Classification`) > 1
  )
GROUP BY
  T1.`School`,
  T1.`Classification`
ORDER BY
  T1.`School`,
  `First_Year_Won_In_Class`;

nl: Calcula la exposición al riesgo por concursante exitoso. Necesito un desglose por ciudad que muestre la ratio de la duración del proceso de producción —es decir, el tiempo desde la primera audición hasta la fecha de emisión— dividida por el número de boletos dorados emitidos. Ordena los resultados de mayor a menor exposición.
sql:
SELECT
  `Audition City`,
  CAST(
    JULIANDAY(
      `Episode_Air_Year` || '-' ||
      printf('%02d', `Episode_Air_Month`) || '-' ||
      printf('%02d', `Episode_Air_Day`)
    ) - JULIANDAY(`Date`) AS REAL
  ) / `Golden Tickets` AS `Risk_Exposure_Per_Ticket`
FROM `table_m_1765007141685_a02e1812_11129123_1`
ORDER BY `Risk_Exposure_Per_Ticket` DESC;
db_sql:
SELECT
  col0,
  CAST(
    JULIANDAY(
      col8 || '-' ||
      printf('%02d', col6) || '-' ||
      printf('%02d', col7)
    ) - JULIANDAY(col1) AS REAL
  ) / col5 AS `Risk_Exposure_Per_Ticket`
FROM `table_m_1765007141685_a02e1812_11129123_1`
ORDER BY `Risk_Exposure_Per_Ticket` DESC;

nl: ¿Cuáles son los títulos y directores de los 5 episodios más recientes que superaron los 18,5 millones de espectadores en EE. UU. y fueron dirigidos por alguien que ha dirigido más de un episodio?
sql:
SELECT T1.`Title`, T1.`Directed by`
FROM `table_m_1765007199989_becd4395_11230937_2` AS T1
WHERE T1.`Directed by` IN (
    SELECT T2.`Directed by`
    FROM `table_m_1765007199989_becd4395_11230937_2` AS T2
    INNER JOIN `table_m_1765007199989_becd4395_11230937_2` AS T3
        ON T2.`Directed by` = T3.`Directed by`
    WHERE T2.`Title` <> T3.`Title`
)
AND CAST(T1.`U.S. viewers (millions)` AS REAL) > 18.5
ORDER BY T1.`No. in series` DESC
LIMIT 5;
db_sql:
SELECT T1.col2, T1.col3
FROM `table_m_1765007199989_becd4395_11230937_2` AS T1
WHERE T1.col3 IN (
    SELECT T2.col3
    FROM `table_m_1765007199989_becd4395_11230937_2` AS T2
    INNER JOIN `table_m_1765007199989_becd4395_11230937_2` AS T3
        ON T2.col3 = T3.col3
    WHERE T2.col2 <> T3.col2
)
AND CAST(T1.col5 AS REAL) > 18.5
ORDER BY T1.col0 DESC
LIMIT 5;

nl: Identifica las cuatro perturbaciones más significativas en el flujo metafísico. Para cada evento, enumera su clave, su fecha, la línea base de energía de la semana anterior, la lectura actual y la magnitud final del flujo.
sql: WITH MetaphysicalFlux AS (SELECT `Episode`, `Air Date`, CAST(`Viewers (m)` AS REAL) AS `Viewers`, LAG(CAST(`Viewers (m)` AS REAL), 1, 0) OVER (ORDER BY `No.`) AS `PreviousViewers` FROM `table_m_1765007277037_2a4b711c_11274401_3`) SELECT `Episode` AS `Event_Key`, `Air Date` AS `Event_Date`, `PreviousViewers`, `Viewers` AS `CurrentViewers`, (`Viewers` - `PreviousViewers`) AS `Flux_Magnitude` FROM MetaphysicalFlux WHERE `PreviousViewers` > 0 ORDER BY ABS(`Flux_Magnitude`) DESC LIMIT 4;
db_sql: WITH MetaphysicalFlux AS (SELECT col1, col2, CAST(col7 AS REAL) AS `Viewers`, LAG(CAST(col7 AS REAL), 1, 0) OVER (ORDER BY col0) AS `PreviousViewers` FROM `table_m_1765007277037_2a4b711c_11274401_3`) SELECT col1 AS `Event_Key`, col2 AS `Event_Date`, `PreviousViewers`, `Viewers` AS `CurrentViewers`, (`Viewers` - `PreviousViewers`) AS `Flux_Magnitude` FROM MetaphysicalFlux WHERE `PreviousViewers` > 0 ORDER BY ABS(`Flux_Magnitude`) DESC LIMIT 4;

nl: ¿Qué pilotos demostraron una clara resonancia cronodinámica, convirtiendo la velocidad punta de una vuelta rápida en una victoria en la siguiente coyuntura temporal? Necesito una lista de estos pilotos, las carreras donde esta resonancia culminó y sus fechas correspondientes.
sql:
WITH `LaggedPerformances` AS (
  SELECT
    `round_number`,
    `Race`,
    `Date`,
    `Race Winner`,
    LAG(`Fastest Lap`, 1) OVER (ORDER BY `round_number`) AS `Previous_Fastest_Lap_Driver`
  FROM
    `table_m_1765007393370_1e3f8f6f_1140076_2`
)
SELECT
  `Race Winner` AS `Driver_With_Momentum`,
  `Race` AS `Winning_Race`,
  `Date` AS `Date_Of_Win`
FROM
  `LaggedPerformances`
WHERE
  `Race Winner` = `Previous_Fastest_Lap_Driver`;
db_sql:
WITH `LaggedPerformances` AS (
  SELECT
    col0,
    col1,
    col2,
    col6,
    LAG(col5, 1) OVER (ORDER BY col0) AS `Previous_Fastest_Lap_Driver`
  FROM `table_m_1765007393370_1e3f8f6f_1140076_2`
)
SELECT
  col6 AS `Driver_With_Momentum`,
  col1 AS `Winning_Race`,
  col2 AS `Date_Of_Win`
FROM
  `LaggedPerformances`
WHERE
  col6 = `Previous_Fastest_Lap_Driver`;

nl: Para cada director que haya dirigido más de un episodio, clasifica su promedio de espectadores en EE. UU. como superior o inferior al promedio general de la serie, y ordénalos en orden descendente según su promedio de espectadores.
sql:
WITH "DirectorStats" AS (
  SELECT
    "Director",
    AVG(CAST("U.S. viewers (millions)" AS REAL)) AS "AverageViewers"
  FROM `table_m_1765007454302_34a2b82c_11404452_1`
  GROUP BY
    "Director"
  HAVING
    COUNT("Series #") > 1
), "Overall" AS (
  SELECT
    AVG(CAST("U.S. viewers (millions)" AS REAL)) AS "GlobalAverage"
  FROM `table_m_1765007454302_34a2b82c_11404452_1`
)
SELECT
  "DirectorStats"."Director",
  CASE
    WHEN "DirectorStats"."AverageViewers" > "Overall"."GlobalAverage" THEN 'Above Average'
    ELSE 'Below Average'
  END AS "ViewerCategory"
FROM "DirectorStats", "Overall"
ORDER BY
  "DirectorStats"."AverageViewers" DESC;
db_sql:
WITH "DirectorStats" AS (
  SELECT
    "Director",
    AVG(CAST("U.S. viewers (millions)" AS REAL)) AS "AverageViewers"
  FROM `table_m_1765007454302_34a2b82c_11404452_1`
  GROUP BY
    "Director"
  HAVING
    COUNT("Series #") > 1
), "Overall" AS (
  SELECT
    AVG(CAST("U.S. viewers (millions)" AS REAL)) AS "GlobalAverage"
  FROM `table_m_1765007454302_34a2b82c_11404452_1`
)
SELECT
  "DirectorStats"."Director",
  CASE
    WHEN "DirectorStats"."AverageViewers" > "Overall"."GlobalAverage" THEN 'Above Average'
    ELSE 'Below Average'
  END AS "ViewerCategory"
FROM "DirectorStats", "Overall"
ORDER BY
  "DirectorStats"."AverageViewers" DESC;
